4. Iterate through the HashMap to build the output string.
5. Return the trimmed output string.

This solution has a time complexity of O(n) because it iterates through the formula once and the parts once. The space complexity is O(n) because it uses a HashMap with a maximum of n elements. The energy implications are low because the algorithm does not consume significant energy.

